meta {
  name: /oob-authenticate
  type: http
  seq: 12
}

post {
  url: {{orgUrl}}/oauth2/{{authorizationServerId}}/v1/oob-authenticate
  body: formUrlEncoded
  auth: basic
}

headers {
  Accept: application/json
}

auth:basic {
  username: {{oauthClientId}}
  password: {{oauthClientSecret}}
}

body:form-urlencoded {
  challenge_hint: urn:okta:params:oauth:grant-type:oob
  channel_hint: push
  login_hint: 
}

docs {
Initiates direct authentication with an out-of-band authenticator

> **Note:** The `/oob-authenticate` endpoint requires client authentication. The method is configured per client app. See [Client authentication methods](/openapi/okta-oauth/guides/client-auth/).

> **Note:** This endpoint is deprecated. Use [/primary-authenticate](/openapi/okta-oauth/oauth/orgas/primary-authenticate) instead.

**Responses:**
- `200`: Out-of-band authentication has successfully been initiated.
- `400`: Bad Request
- `401`: Unauthorized
- `403`: Forbidden
- `429`: Too Many Requests
}
